Answer:
gpt_response: The chemical name for CC(CCN)(C1CCN(C1)C)F is fluoxetine. It is a selective serotonin reuptake inhibitor (SSRI) commonly used as an antidepressant medication in the treatment of major depressive disorder, panic disorder, and other mental health conditions. Its chemical structure consists of a trifluoromethylphenyl ring attached to a diazepane ring through a nitrogen atom.
